table.column: Parts of an ax include its handle, {DeS:n:2}, and its blade, {ghIt:n:2}.

table.name: mem
table.column: This refers to a person who puts in pipes (whether for water or for anything else). There is a special word for a pipe that carries water, {qatlhDa':n}, but the person who puts this in is still called an {'och mutlhwI':n:nolink}.

table.name: mem
table.column: "Ode to Spot" is the name of a poem Data wrote to his cat, Spot.

table.name: mem
table.column: This word implies the creation of something which has not been created before. In this, it differs from {ren:v}.

table.name: mem
table.column: он, она, оно, его, её (для вещей, не способных использовать речь)

table.name: mem
table.column: verify, check if (something) is true, make sure that (something) is true
überprüfen, kontrollieren, prüfen ob etwas wahr bzw. richtig ist
驗證，檢查（某事）是否為真，確保（某事）是真的 [AUTOTRANSLATED]
Note that {'ol:v:nolink} is used for checking a fact, while {woq:v} is used for confirming it.
The {TKD:src} definition says only "verify". This was expanded upon at {Saarbrücken qepHom'a' 2017:src}.

table.name: mem
table.column:
This can refer to the space between your teeth or the area between rows of seats in a theatre, but it (and {'olQanmey:n@@'olQan:n, -mey:n}) can be used for the space in a room, on a desk, etc.
A verb commonly used with {'olQan:n:nolink} is {'uch:v:1}.

table.name: mem
table.column: "Ohm" is the unit of electrical resistance.

table.name: mem
mem
table.column: This can be used for sinking into water and so on.

table.name: mem
table.column:
Verbs related to aircraft (or spacecraft) movement include: {Dav:v}, {Der:v}, {jer:v}, {jIm:v}, {lol:v:2}, {ron:v}, {tor:v:2}.
It is unknown if all of these words have meanings outside of the context of aircraft attitude descriptions. However, {ron:v:nolink} can be applied to other objects such as dice (see {mI' nagh:n}), and {lol:v:nolink} and {tor:v:nolink} can be applied to people or animals (see {lol:v:1} and {tor:v:1}).

table.name: mem
table.column: This is also called {'orghenya':n:nolink}, typically by older speakers.[2]

table.name: mem
table.column:
Note that this is {'orghengan:n:nolink} and not {'orghenngan:n:nolink} (the {n:sen:nolink} at the end of {'orghen:n:nolink} is dropped).
This word is also written {'orghenya'ngan:n:nolink}.

table.name: mem
table.column: This refers to any place a vessel is moored, even if there is no structure.
"The Tragedy of Othello, the Moor of Venice" is a play by William Shakespeare.

table.column: quantum theory, quantum mechanics, quantum physics
量子理論，量子力學，量子物理 [AUTOTRANSLATED]
This was first defined as "quantum theory, quantum mechanics" in 2014, and subsequently as "quantum physics" in 2015.

table.name: mem
table.column: In 2014, following the definition of {'otlhQeD:n}, this was glossed as "the corresponding scientist, someone who studies quantum mechanics". It was subsequently given the stand-alone definition of "quantum physicist" in 2015.

table.name: mem
table.column: This is spelled "painstik" (without the "c") throughout Star Trek canon, except in {TKDA:src} where it is spelled "painstick".

table.column: If you don't use the painstik, the child will never celebrate his Age of Ascension.
Wenn du den Schmerzstock nicht benutzt, wird das Kind nie das Aufstiegsalter zelebrieren.
如果你不使用painstik，孩子將永遠不會慶祝他的提升時代。 [AUTOTRANSLATED]

table.column: This idiomatic expression literally means "My little toe aches a lot". See {Qay':v:2} for an explanation.

table.column: For the area behind an object, see {'em:n}.

table.name: mem
table.column: The {'o' chuyDaH:n:nolink} is located near the {Hongghor:n}. They are listed together as {'o' chuyDaH Hongghor je:n:nolink} on the {BoP:src} poster.

table.name: mem
table.column: This is a drum with skin stretched over both ends.[1, p.75]

table.name: mem
table.column:
This word is only used for songs. The final phrase or portion in other kinds of performances is referred to using {bertlham:n}.
All Klingon songs have {'o'meghmey:n:nolink}. If a song fades away instead of properly ending, as some Federation songs do, the ending of such a song may be called {'o'meghqoq:n:nolink}.

table.name: mem
table.column: This is a reference to O. Roy Chalk.

table.name: mem
table.column: Jemand mit zweideutigem oder undeutlichem Stand
某人（或某事）具有模棱兩可的地位 [AUTOTRANSLATED]
This term can be used for "double agent" (for which a slang term is {jey'naS ghoqwI':n}), but its meaning is a bit broader.
Possibly a reference to Owen Lattimore, who was accused under McCarthyism of being a spy.
